1
00:01:54,223 --> 00:01:57,892
<i>(Madara)</i>
<i>This place was known</i>
<i>as the "Training Cave"</i>

2
00:01:57,925 --> 00:02:00,528
{\an1}Hey, tell me about
this new jutsu.

3
00:02:00,561 --> 00:02:05,497
{\an1}What exactly does this
Limited Tsukuyomi do?

4
00:02:05,531 --> 00:02:09,501
{\an1}And experimental version
of the Infinite Tsukuyomi.

5
00:02:09,535 --> 00:02:14,438
{\an1}First, we need to
understand the true
desires of our target.

6
00:02:21,277 --> 00:02:23,378
Hm.

7
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:33,253
{\an1}<i>(Naruto)</i>
<i>I can't believe it's the</i>
<i>last day of my R & R!</i>

8
00:02:33,286 --> 00:02:37,788
{\an4}All right!I need to
re-energize for tomorrow
so it's time for me to
but out that limited

9
00:02:37,822 --> 00:02:41,459
{\an1}edition premium ramen
that I've been saving for
a time just like this!

10
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:48,797
{\an1}[goofy happy laughs]

11
00:02:49,632 --> 00:02:52,233
{\an1}Man, am I bored.

12
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:53,334
{\an1}Wait..!

13
00:02:54,901 --> 00:02:58,205
{\an1}Ha! Tadah! Guess
what this is!

14
00:02:58,238 --> 00:03:00,641
{\an1}Whoa, no way! It's
that premium ramen!

15
00:03:00,674 --> 00:03:03,643
Every store's sold out
of it! You can't find
it anywhere anymore!

16
00:03:03,676 --> 00:03:06,244
{\an1}Well, today's your
lucky day, 'cause
you get to have some!

17
00:03:06,278 --> 00:03:07,512
{\an1}Are you in, or what!?

18
00:03:07,545 --> 00:03:08,580
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

19
00:03:08,613 --> 00:03:10,748
{\an1}Do ya really want some!?

20
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:11,948
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

21
00:03:11,981 --> 00:03:14,350
Really, <i>really </i>
want some--?

22
00:03:14,384 --> 00:03:16,586
{\an5}-Yeah! C'mon!
Cook it up!
-Yeah! C'mon!
Cook it up!

23
00:03:16,619 --> 00:03:19,655
{\an1}Well then, let's
play some cards!

24
00:03:19,688 --> 00:03:22,423
{\an1}And whoever wins
gets to have the
ramen as a prize!

25
00:03:22,456 --> 00:03:24,492
Yay! Awesome!

26
00:03:26,526 --> 00:03:28,595
[sigh] I'm so tired.

27
00:03:28,628 --> 00:03:32,531
{\an5}But, at long last,
the mission's over
and I finally get
a break tomorrow!

28
00:03:32,564 --> 00:03:35,700
{\an1}Oh, Kakashi! Please
do me a favor and
take over, okay?

29
00:03:35,733 --> 00:03:38,001
Sure, sure.
Roger that.

30
00:03:38,035 --> 00:03:41,405
{\an5}I really need
to go unwind.
How about the
bathhouse?

31
00:03:41,438 --> 00:03:44,806
{\an1}Hm. Lee, are you
coming with us?

32
00:03:44,839 --> 00:03:46,141
Thank you,
but I cannot!

33
00:03:46,174 --> 00:03:49,477
{\an1}Now that the mission
is over, I must get
back to training!

34
00:03:49,511 --> 00:03:50,811
{\an1}That's admirable.

35
00:03:50,844 --> 00:03:54,315
{\an4}But listen, don't
overdo it, or your
body won't be able
to keep--

36
00:03:54,348 --> 00:03:57,684
{\an1}[happy sob] That's my
dedicated boy, Lee!

37
00:03:57,717 --> 00:04:01,886
{\an1}You're brimming with
youth! Yes! Yes! Yes!

38
00:04:01,919 --> 00:04:04,756
{\an1}Whaddaya say we
train together!?

39
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:05,855
{\an4}<i>(Guy)</i>
<i>Let's go!</i>
<i>(Lee)</i>
<i>Right!</i>

40
00:04:05,889 --> 00:04:07,692
Are they okay?

41
00:04:07,725 --> 00:04:12,729
{\an1}Follow me! We'll rush
forward with the full
power of youth!

42
00:04:12,762 --> 00:04:15,597
Ahhhh!

43
00:04:16,565 --> 00:04:19,267
Nope. Just as
I thought...

44
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,535
Ahh! Guy Sensei!

45
00:04:21,568 --> 00:04:24,604
Get up! Please!
You have to get up!

46
00:04:24,638 --> 00:04:26,372
You must face tomorrow!

47
00:04:26,405 --> 00:04:30,408
{\an1}Lee... his body simply
won't do what he tells
it anymore.

48
00:04:30,442 --> 00:04:31,975
Please do not die!!!

49
00:04:32,009 --> 00:04:33,812
No! Guy Sensei!!!

50
00:04:33,844 --> 00:04:37,614
You made me a promise
that you would make
me a fine shinobi!

51
00:04:37,648 --> 00:04:39,949
{\an1}[sigh] Lee, listen.

52
00:04:39,982 --> 00:04:45,721
{\an4}I'll take over looking
after Guy, but can you
take a message from me
to Sakura and Naruto!?

53
00:04:45,754 --> 00:04:46,387
Huh..?

54
00:04:47,388 --> 00:04:49,523
{\an1}Do you have to
be so messy!?

55
00:04:49,557 --> 00:04:53,326
{\an1}Why can't you line
up the seams when
you fold laundry!?

56
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,060
Do it yourself
if you're going
to complain!

57
00:04:55,094 --> 00:04:58,963
{\an5}I really don't need
to hear a bunch of
useless lectures from
you on my day off!

58
00:04:58,996 --> 00:05:01,566
{\an1}The only time you're
ever home is on your
day off!

59
00:05:01,599 --> 00:05:02,633
<i>(Sakura)</i>
<i>Duh, of course.</i>

60
00:05:02,667 --> 00:05:04,067
{\an1}<i>(Mebuki)</i>
<i>Don't you talk</i>
<i>back to me--!</i>

61
00:05:04,101 --> 00:05:06,103
[groan]

62
00:05:06,136 --> 00:05:09,338
{\an5}<i>(Kizashi)</i>
<i>Sakura, you need to</i>
<i>listen to your mother.</i>
<i>She's absolutely correct.</i>

63
00:05:09,372 --> 00:05:12,808
{\an1}So stop arguing with
her, and don't be so
salty!

64
00:05:13,808 --> 00:05:14,743
Salt... get it!?

65
00:05:18,479 --> 00:05:20,480
{\an1}[groan]

66
00:05:20,514 --> 00:05:22,048
Lee, what's up?

67
00:05:22,081 --> 00:05:25,617
{\an5}Uhh, sorry to
interrupt but, I
have a message...
about your mission.

68
00:05:25,650 --> 00:05:29,855
Ohhh, you must mean
the prep meeting for
our next mission!

69
00:05:29,887 --> 00:05:31,589
I'll be right there!

70
00:05:34,457 --> 00:05:36,760
Sorry. I did not
want to bother you--

71
00:05:36,793 --> 00:05:39,628
{\an1}But the message is for
you to meet tomorrow
morning at six.

72
00:05:39,661 --> 00:05:42,563
{\an1}It's okay. You gave me
a good excuse to leave!

73
00:05:42,597 --> 00:05:48,835
{\an1}[stretching] I really
just wanted to take
it easy today, ya know?

74
00:05:48,869 --> 00:05:51,704
{\an1}So, thank you, Lee!

75
00:05:53,672 --> 00:05:55,106
{\an1}Now... the next stop!

76
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:56,974
Yes!! I win!!

77
00:05:57,007 --> 00:05:59,443
I'm not having
any luck at all!

78
00:05:59,476 --> 00:06:02,746
{\an1}Oh boy, that was
a close call! I
almost went in!

79
00:06:02,780 --> 00:06:05,815
Listen, you! You
better not be cheating!

80
00:06:05,848 --> 00:06:09,384
{\an1}It's always the weak
ones who complain!

81
00:06:09,418 --> 00:06:10,685
What was that--!?

82
00:06:10,719 --> 00:06:13,587
{\an1}Cut it out, ya
know? You're all
me, so get along!

83
00:06:13,621 --> 00:06:15,689
Hey, who's side are
you on, anyway!?

84
00:06:15,723 --> 00:06:17,023
{\an1}Well now that
you ask...

85
00:06:17,056 --> 00:06:19,492
I demand we start
the game over!

86
00:06:19,526 --> 00:06:21,727
The loser sure
knows how to whine!

87
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:24,696
All right that's
it! Let's go outside!

88
00:06:24,730 --> 00:06:25,630
{\an1}[groan]

89
00:06:29,666 --> 00:06:30,667
{\an1}Huh!?

90
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:34,036
{\an1}Wait, I have no
idea if I won or
lost that game!

91
00:06:36,971 --> 00:06:39,407
{\an1}[weary sigh]

92
00:06:44,845 --> 00:06:48,614
{\an1}What am I doin'
hangin' out here by myself
on my last day off?

93
00:06:50,615 --> 00:06:54,051
{\an1}Boy, it sure does
get lonely around
here sometimes...

94
00:06:56,986 --> 00:06:58,421
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Naruto... </i>

95
00:06:58,622 --> 00:07:00,857
{\an1}<i>(Choji)</i>
<i>Please, let's go</i>
<i>to Barbe-Q's!</i>

96
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:04,560
{\an4}They're doing this all-
you-can-eat special for
fifteen hundred ryo per
table--

97
00:07:04,593 --> 00:07:07,896
{\an1}--So even if we split
it between the three
of us, it's only...

98
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:09,664
{\an1}Let's see... it's uhh...

99
00:07:09,697 --> 00:07:11,164
{\an1}Five hundred ryo.

100
00:07:11,198 --> 00:07:15,167
{\an1}We just completed a
mission. I'd rather have
a soak than food right now.

101
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:17,203
{\an1}Yeah, I vote
for a soak, too!

102
00:07:17,236 --> 00:07:21,506
{\an5}<i>(Kiba)</i>
<i>Akamaru, You're more</i>
<i>dirt than dog, now! I</i>
<i>should call you "Chamaru!"</i>

103
00:07:21,539 --> 00:07:23,808
Get it? 'Cause
"cha" means "brown"

104
00:07:23,842 --> 00:07:25,375
[whimper]

105
00:07:25,409 --> 00:07:31,647
{\an1}Actually, Akamaru should
never be called Akamaru,
because his name means "red."

106
00:07:31,681 --> 00:07:36,450
{\an1}So instead, Akamaru should
be called "Shiromaru" because
"shiro" means "white."

107
00:07:36,484 --> 00:07:38,652
I don't have any
idea what you're
yapping about!

108
00:07:38,686 --> 00:07:42,121
{\an5}All I was saying
is that Akamaru is
filthy and that I
need to clean him up!

109
00:07:42,155 --> 00:07:43,623
Ever heard of a
sense of humor?

110
00:07:43,656 --> 00:07:46,792
{\an4}Then you ought to
bring him to the
bathhouse with the
rest of us!

111
00:07:46,825 --> 00:07:50,728
{\an1}Impossible... Dogs
are never allowed
in the bathhouse.

112
00:07:50,761 --> 00:07:53,497
<i>(Kiba)</i>
<i>Well I'll just have to</i>
<i>figure something out! </i>

113
00:07:53,530 --> 00:07:54,598
[gasp]

114
00:07:54,631 --> 00:07:57,433
I really need to
go unwind. How about
the bathhouse?

115
00:07:58,534 --> 00:07:59,869
{\an1}Ahhh!

116
00:07:59,902 --> 00:08:03,104
{\an1}Naruto! Listen! Let us
gather everyone and
go to the bathhouse!

117
00:08:03,137 --> 00:08:10,911
{\an4}Everyone! We should all
go to the bathhouse
together and unwind in the
company of true friends!

118
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:17,749
{\an1}I don't get it. Lee's
the one who suggested
this. Why isn't he here?

119
00:08:17,782 --> 00:08:21,919
{\an4}He;s not done training
yet. He still has to
walk three thousand
steps on his hands.

120
00:08:21,952 --> 00:08:24,220
{\an1}He said he'll come
once he finishes.

121
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:26,422
{\an1}He sure is
dedicated...

122
00:08:26,456 --> 00:08:31,125
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Bushy Brows was being</i>
<i>thoughtful because he saw</i>
<i>that I was all by myself.</i>

123
00:08:31,158 --> 00:08:34,529
{\an1}I just really hope
he gets here soon!

124
00:08:40,834 --> 00:08:46,005
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Just when I thought</i>
<i>I could relax by myself.</i>

125
00:08:46,037 --> 00:08:47,939
{\an7}<i>Oh well, whatever!</i>

126
00:08:47,972 --> 00:08:53,977
{\an4}[sigh] Nothing like
a hot soak to warm
your tired boned
after a mission..!

127
00:08:54,011 --> 00:08:56,244
{\an1}Tenten, you sound like
an old man or something!

128
00:08:56,278 --> 00:08:58,647
[giggle]

129
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,080
{\an1}[embarrassed gasp]

130
00:09:00,114 --> 00:09:05,151
{\an1}Hinata! Just relax.
Don't be embarrassed
and try to hide yourself!

131
00:09:05,184 --> 00:09:07,487
{\an1}We're all women here.

132
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,857
<i>(Sakura)</i>
<i>Just sink in and</i>
<i>enjoy the bath!</i>

133
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:13,859
{\an1}Oh... Umm... I...

134
00:09:15,927 --> 00:09:17,260
[gasp]

135
00:09:17,295 --> 00:09:20,230
{\an1}But... they just
keep floating up!

136
00:09:22,832 --> 00:09:26,200
[groan]

137
00:09:26,234 --> 00:09:29,203
{\an8}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Is it wrong that I'm</i>
<i>jealous of Hinata..?</i>

138
00:09:29,237 --> 00:09:31,940
{\an8}<i>...of her chest</i>
<i>that is...</i>

139
00:09:32,873 --> 00:09:35,541
I must hurry!

140
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,176
{\an1}One thousand eight-
hundred fifty-two!

141
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:40,745
{\an1}One thousand eight-
hundred fifty-three!

142
00:09:40,779 --> 00:09:42,112
{\an1}One thousand eight-
hundred fifty-four!

143
00:09:44,315 --> 00:09:46,917
{\an1}I wonder if Bushy-Brows
is still at it...

144
00:09:46,951 --> 00:09:50,253
He's a hard worker,
but he can't read
people too well...

145
00:09:50,286 --> 00:09:54,790
{\an4}That's not unusual.
And why is that, you
ask? Because he's a
worker ant.

146
00:09:55,189 --> 00:09:59,160
{\an1}And boy, do I ever
love ants like that.

147
00:09:59,193 --> 00:10:02,063
{\an1}You must look at
your comrades in a
more generous light.

148
00:10:04,631 --> 00:10:06,131
{\an7}<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>this guy...</i>

149
00:10:06,165 --> 00:10:09,969
{\an7}<i>He's actually still</i>
<i>bitter from the time</i>
<i>that he was left out</i>
<i>of that mission!</i>

150
00:10:10,002 --> 00:10:12,704
{\an1}Wow, Shino! What a
nice thing to say!

151
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:14,671
{\an1}You sure have a big--

152
00:10:19,175 --> 00:10:21,877
{\an1}Ahhhhh!

153
00:10:21,911 --> 00:10:26,848
{\an4}That's so disgusting!
Shino! Don't look now,
but there's a giant
larva near your groin!

154
00:10:26,881 --> 00:10:30,050
{\an1}He's an insect user,
of course some of them
will end up on his body!

155
00:10:30,084 --> 00:10:31,651
Oh!

156
00:10:31,684 --> 00:10:36,722
{\an1}Shino, you're one of the
guys that I really look up
to... in more ways than one!

157
00:10:36,755 --> 00:10:38,155
Hm? Really?

158
00:10:38,189 --> 00:10:40,224
Hey, did ya hear
that, Kiba?

159
00:10:41,325 --> 00:10:42,593
Huh?

160
00:10:42,627 --> 00:10:43,928
{\an1}[barking]

161
00:10:43,961 --> 00:10:44,394
Huh!?

162
00:10:44,427 --> 00:10:46,096
